<hl>
<seg id=1> By November, the foreign fund used in China had 27% increases. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, 17 December Although by November the projects and the funds of foreign capital had decreased this year, the actual foreign funds used this year had 27.1% increase compared with the same period last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to the figures from the Ministry of Economic Co-operation and Foreign Trade today, by this December, the actual foreign capital used in China was US$ 46.959 billion among which there was US$ 40.7 billion from the direct investment of the foreign businessmen. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> By this November, there were 18,644 projects from the foreign capital; it had decreased by 15% compared with the same period last year. The total foreign funds were US$ 48.462 billion, and it had decreased by 27.14%. </seg>
<seg id=5> Among the newly approved joint enterprises, the number of the jointly-operated and cooperated enterprises of national and foreign capital dropped, but the number of the pure foreign enterprises was 8,484 and increased by 4.12%. </seg>
<seg id=6> The actual foreign funds increased by 30% over the same period last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Until this November, the newly approved co-operation projects with foreign businessmen were 13, but there were 10 in the same period last year. </seg>
<seg id=8> The assigned foreign funds and the actual foreign funds used were US$250 million and US$311 million, which were 14.53% and 61.98% over last year. </seg>
</p>
